    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Incorrect MCS Selection in Network Simulator Not Matching Channel Quality\n\n### Summary\nThe network simulator in the NAS testing framework was using a fixed QCI value of 3 for all EPS bearer setups, regardless of the reported channel quality (RSRP/RSRQ). This caused inappropriate MCS selection downstream of the `_process_ul_info_transfer_req` function, as the fixed QCI did not reflect the actual channel conditions or UE capabilities.\n\nWhen testing with varying channel conditions, this led to suboptimal resource allocation and unrealistic simulation behavior. The simulator would always configure bearers with QCI 3 (real-time gaming) even under poor channel conditions where a more tolerant QCI would be appropriate.\n\nThe fix implements adaptive QCI selection based on the DEFAULT_RSRP and DEFAULT_RSRQ values, mapping them to appropriate CQI values and then to QCI values that better match the channel quality.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/TEST/NETWORK/network_simulator.c`: \n  * Added `_map_channel_quality_to_cqi()` function to map RSRP/RSRQ to CQI values\n  * Added `_map_cqi_to_qci()` function to map CQI to appropriate QCI based on channel quality\n  * Modified `_process_pdn_connectivity_request()` to use adaptive QCI selection instead of hardcoded value\n"
}